# iM.Cloud Architecture

Self-hosted cloud storage (.NET 9, Clean Architecture). Follow `PROJECT_PLAN.md` for scope and phases.

## Layer Dependencies (strict)

| Layer | May reference | Must NOT reference |
|-------|---------------|-------------------|
| Domain | nothing | Application, Infrastructure, API, EF Core, ASP.NET |
| Application | Domain | Infrastructure, API |
| Infrastructure | Application, Domain | API |
| API | Application, Infrastructure (DI only) | direct DB/storage calls |

Dependency flow: `Domain ← Application ← Infrastructure ← API`.

## File Placement

Place new code in the correct project under `src/`:

- `iM.Cloud.Domain/` — entities, value objects, domain enums
- `iM.Cloud.Application/` — use cases (Command/Query + Handler), DTOs, interfaces (`IFileStorageService`, `IAuthService`, etc.)
- `iM.Cloud.Infrastructure/` — EF Core, MinIO, JWT/BCrypt implementations
- `iM.Cloud.API/` — controllers, middleware, `Program.cs` only

Register services via each layer's `DependencyInjection.cs` (`AddApplication`, `AddInfrastructure`).

## Use Case Pattern

- One Command or Query class per use case — no large god-services
- Handlers injected via DI — **no MediatR or other mediator libraries**
- Auth handlers return `Result` or `Result<T>` from `Application.Common.Models`
- Admin CRUD returns BaseCrud `ServiceResult` via `IEfCrudService` / `ICrudService` implementations
- API controllers delegate to handlers (auth) or BaseCrud services (admin CRUD) — no business logic in controllers

## Domain Entities

- Private setters + static factory methods (`CreateFile`, `CreateFolder`)
- Never `new Entity()` from outside the entity class

## Storage Rules

- Folder hierarchy lives in SQL (`FileItem`: `ParentId`, `IsFolder`)
- File blobs live in MinIO (`StorageKey = {userId}/{fileId}`)
- Application talks to storage only through `IFileStorageService`
- Upload order: MinIO first, then SQL; rollback MinIO blob if SQL fails

## Security (non-negotiable)

- Check owner/permission on every file operation (IDOR protection)
- Recursive delete for folders (SQL + MinIO cascade)
- Validate file names (non-empty, length, no control characters)
- Secrets never in `appsettings.json` — use `dotnet user-secrets` (dev) or environment variables (prod)

## Minimalism

- Do not add NuGet packages, patterns, or libraries without asking first
- No test projects in MVP — verify with `dotnet build`
- `TargetFramework`, `Nullable`, `ImplicitUsings` are set in `Directory.Build.props` — do not duplicate in csproj files

## English Only

All code artifacts must be in English:

- Comments, identifiers, string literals, log messages, exception messages
- Commit messages and PR descriptions

## After Changes

Run `dotnet build` from the solution root and fix any errors before finishing.

## API errors and FE notifications

See `.cursor/rules/service-result-errors.mdc` — use BaseCrud `ServiceResult` / `ServiceError` with translation keys in both `ErrorMessage` and `ErrorKey`; FE resolves via translation service.
